s-active-low-which-inverts-the-mental-model-of-signal-received-equals-pin-high","target":"ir-demodulator-output-is-active-low-which-inverts-the-mental-model-of-signal-received-equals-pin-high","line":34},{"title":"wiring-integration","target":"wiring-integration","line":37},{"title":"eda-fundamentals","target":"eda-fundamentals","line":38},{"title":"breadboard-intelligence","target":"breadboard-intelligence","line":39}],"metadata":{"description":"When a 74HC14 or similar inverting buffer is inserted between MCU and load for isolation, the firmware must invert every output command on those pins — what looks like digitalWrite(HIGH) produces LOW at the load, and forgetting the inversion makes the motor do the opposite of what was intended","type":"claim","source":"docs/parts/wiring-nodemcu-esp32-to-4x-zs-x11h-for-4wd-rover.md","confidence":"proven","topics":["[[wiring-integration]]","[[eda-fundamentals]]","[[breadboard-intelligence]]"],"related_components":[]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[]},